## `playbooks/aap_cleanup.yml`

**Purpose:** Remove **only** objects this demo created. Destructive; requires explicit confirmation.

### Default approach: explicit `ansible.controller` deletes

- Single play: `hosts: localhost`, `connection: local`, `gather_facts: false`.
- Collections: `ansible.controller`, `ansible.builtin`.
- Same `vars_files` as `aap_config.yml`.
- Reusable auth anchor (prefer `controller_host` / `validate_certs`, not legacy `controller_hostname`):

```yaml
  vars:
    controller_auth: &controller_auth
      controller_host: "https://{{ aap_hostname }}"
      controller_username: "{{ aap_username }}"
      controller_password: "{{ aap_password }}"
      validate_certs: "{{ aap_validate_certs }}"
```

- **Confirmation** in `pre_tasks` (tag `always`):

```yaml
  pre_tasks:
    - name: Require demo_cleanup_confirm=true before removing AAP objects
      ansible.builtin.assert:
        that:
          - demo_cleanup_confirm | default(false) | bool
        fail_msg: >-
          Refusing to run cleanup. Pass -e demo_cleanup_confirm=true to
          remove demo organizations, projects, templates, and inventories.
      tags:
        - always
```

Run command to document:

```bash
ansible-playbook playbooks/aap_cleanup.yml -e demo_cleanup_confirm=true --vault-id @prompt
```

### NEVER use dispatch with `platform_state: absent` when labels are defined

**`ansible.controller.label` does not support `state: absent`.** If the demo defines
`controller_labels` in `group_vars/all/labels.yml`, dispatch with `platform_state: absent`
will crash with:

```
value of state must be one of: present, exists, got: absent
```

**The explicit `ansible.controller` approach (above) is always the safe default.** Use
dispatch absent only for demos that have **zero** label definitions — which in practice
means almost never, since labels are standard in every demo scaffold.

### Alternative approach: dispatch cleanup

Kept for reference. Only valid when the demo has **no** `controller_labels` defined,
no custom credential types, no manual post-CasC objects, and no EDA on Controller.

```yaml
---
- name: Confirm demo cleanup
  hosts: localhost
  gather_facts: false
  collections:
    - ansible.builtin
  tasks:
    - name: Require demo_cleanup_confirm=true before removing AAP objects
      ansible.builtin.assert:
        that:
          - demo_cleanup_confirm | default(false) | bool
        fail_msg: Pass -e demo_cleanup_confirm=true to run cleanup.
      tags:
        - always

- name: Remove demo configuration from AAP
  hosts: localhost
  gather_facts: false
  collections:
    - infra.aap_configuration
    - ansible.builtin
  vars_files:
    - ../vault.yml
    - ../group_vars/all/demo_variables.yml
  vars:
    platform_state: absent
  roles:
    - role: infra.aap_configuration.dispatch
```

Pick **one** cleanup strategy per demo; do not mix dispatch absent with manual deletes for the same objects.

### Deletion order (explicit cleanup)

Number sections `# --- N. ... ---`. Every delete: `state: absent`, `ignore_errors: true`, `<<: *controller_auth`, resource-type tag.

| Step | Resource | Module | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Workflow job templates | `ansible.controller.workflow_job_template` | |
| 2 | Job templates | `ansible.controller.job_template` | Include **legacy names** in the loop if templates were renamed |
| 3 | Inventory sources | `ansible.controller.inventory_source` | **Before** inventories |
| 4 | Inventories (children, then parents) | `ansible.controller.inventory` | Delete constructed/parent inventories after children |
| 5 | Project | `ansible.controller.project` | |
| 6 | Credentials | `ansible.controller.credential` | Loop `{name, type}`; include Hub/registry creds when created |
| 7 | Custom credential types | `ansible.controller.credential_type` | After credentials that reference them |
| 8 | Execution environments | `ansible.controller.execution_environment` | |
| 9 | Users / teams | `ansible.controller.user` / `.team` | When demo CasC creates RBAC objects |
| 10 | Labels | **Skip** — debug task only | No direct delete API |
| last | Organization | `ansible.controller.organization` | |

**Labels skip task (required):**

```yaml
    - name: Labels will be removed with the organization
      ansible.builtin.debug:
        msg: "Skipping labels — no direct delete API; removed with organization."
      tags:
        - labels
```

**Post-task:** short debug summary with re-deploy command (`aap_config.yml`). If EDA objects exist, point to **`playbooks/eda_cleanup.yml`** instead of deleting EDA from `aap_cleanup.yml` (EDA drift-detection pattern).

### EDA cleanup

Use a dedicated **`playbooks/eda_cleanup.yml`** with its own confirmation extra var (e.g. `confirm_eda_delete=DELETE-EDA` or align to `demo_cleanup_confirm` if you standardize later). Remove activations before projects/credentials. Reference it from Controller cleanup post-tasks and README.

---

## Cross-playbook consistency

- Object names in cleanup must match `group_vars/all/` and job/workflow template names in CasC.
- README **Quick start** → `aap_config.yml`; **Reset / teardown** → `aap_cleanup.yml` with confirmation extra var.
- Do not omit `vault.yml` from `vars_files` when credentials or post-tasks need secrets.

## Out of scope

- Data-plane playbooks (`playbooks/demo/`, `site.yml`, `verify.yml`).
- Cloud resource teardown playbooks (`playbooks/cleanup/`) — separate from AAP object cleanup.
- Hub/gateway-only cleanup unless CasC creates those objects.
